        descLong: "Web Storage provides simple client-side key-value storage. localStorage persists across browser restarts (until cleared). sessionStorage clears when the tab closes. Both are limited to ~5-10MB and store only strings (JSON.stringify for objects). storage events fire when data changes in other tabs. Synchronous access can block the main thread — for large data, use IndexedDB instead.",
