                            "code": "// === ENTRY-LEVEL EXAMPLE ===\n// TASK      - Basic usage of Web Share API — Native Sharing — understand the core syntax and behavior.\n// APPROACH  - Simple example with minimal parameters; no edge cases.\n// STRENGTHS - Clear, readable; shows the fundamental pattern.\n// WEAKNESSES- Not production-ready; no error handling or complex scenarios.\n// APPROACH  - the simplest Web Share: check for support, then open the OS share sheet.\n// STRENGTHS - five lines; shows feature detection + navigator.share with title/url.\n// WEAKNESSES- no fallback, no error handling, no canShare check.\n//\n// GOAL: open the native OS share sheet\n// WHY: navigator.share gives users their installed apps as share targets (no custom UI needed)\nif (navigator.share) {\n  await navigator.share({\n    title: 'Check this out',\n    url: 'https://example.com',\n  });\n}"
